RECOMMENDED: Diminishing same-day returns (preferred over hard cooldown)

Approach A — DIMINISHING RETURNS (recommended):
  Track per-player: last_upgrade_date, upgrades_today_count
  Each additional upgrade in same 24h period gets progressively less effective:
    1st upgrade: 100% gain (full multiplier)
    2nd upgrade: 50% gain
    3rd upgrade: 25% gain
    4th+: minimum gain only (1 point per stat)
  Reset counter at midnight UTC.

  In upgradesService.js upgrade():
    const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
    const count = player.upgrades_today_count || 0;
    const isNewDay = player.last_upgrade_date !== today;
    const effectiveCount = isNewDay ? 0 : count;
    const diminishFactor = Math.pow(0.5, effectiveCount); // 1.0, 0.5, 0.25, 0.125...
    // Apply diminishFactor to the upgrade gain calculation
    const gain = Math.max(1, Math.round(baseGain * diminishFactor));
    player.upgrades_today_count = effectiveCount + 1;
    player.last_upgrade_date = today;

Approach B — HARD COOLDOWN (simpler but less whale-friendly):
  Max 1 booster per player per 24 hours.
  Max 3 booster uses per club per day (across all players).
  Store last_upgrade_at timestamp on player record.
  In upgrade(): if (Date.now() - player.last_upgrade_at < 86400000) throw 'Upgrade on cooldown';

Approach A is preferred because it still allows spending (revenue) while protecting balance.
